    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MINORITIES STOPPED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PETER BELLER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Beller, Peter</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey State Police, complying with Justice Department agreement in racial profiling case, releases figures showing that troopers stopped minorities on turnpike more often than anywhere else in state during first four months of year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Troopers stopped minorities on the turnpike more often than anywhere else in the state during the first four months of this year, according to figures released last week by the State Police. The report said that 38 percent of drivers stopped on the turnpike were nonwhite, compared with 26 percent statewide. It was submitted to comply with an agreement with the federal Justice Department in a racial profiling case last year,</p>
        <p>PETER BELLER</p>
      </block>
